<deviceset name="DS1077" prefix="U" urn="urn:adsk.eagle:component:38772049/1">
<description>&lt;h3&gt;Maxim DS1077 - I2C Real-time clock (RTC)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The   DS1077   is   a   dual-output,   programmable,   fixed-frequency   oscillator   requiring   no   external   components for operation. The DS1077 can be used as a processor-controlled frequency synthesizer or as  a  standalone  oscillator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The  DS1077  features  a  2-wire  serial  interface  that  allows  in-circuit  on-the-fly  programming  of the  programmable  prescalers  (P0  &amp;  P1)  and  divider  (N)  with  the  desired  values  being  stored  in  NV  (EEPROM)   memory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SparkFun Products:
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.sparkfun.com/products/retired/99"&gt;Real Time Clock Module&lt;/a&gt; (BOB-00099)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://datasheets.maximintegrated.com/en/ds/DS1077.pdf"&gt;Datasheet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<gates>
<gate name="G$1" symbol="DS1077" x="0" y="0"/>
</gates>
<devices>
<device name="U" package="SO08-0.15">
<connects>
<connect gate="G$1" pin="CTRL0" pad="5"/>
<connect gate="G$1" pin="CTRL1" pad="6"/>
